      • dispatchCallback

        public void dispatchCallback(java.lang.String objectUuid,
                             java.lang.String callbackUuid,
                             java.lang.String... args)
        We *previously* called a method on some JavaScriptProxyObject that required a callback. The called JavaScript method is now calling that callback. Here we just delegate back to a static JavaScriptProxyObject method to figure out what to do.
        Parameters:
        objectUuid - - the UUID of the object that owns the callback object to be called
        callbackUuid - - the UUID of the callback
        args - - the parameters to the callback (as JSON)

      • callMethodOnNativeObject

        public void callMethodOnNativeObject(java.lang.String uuid,
                                     java.lang.String methodName,
                                     java.lang.String pendingResultUuid,
                                     java.lang.String json)
        It is possible to make a call to JavaScript passing in an object that JS can in turn make method calls This method is the call that JavaScript will make to execute a method on such a passed-in object. See more details in JavaScriptProxyObject
        Parameters:
        uuid - the uuid of the object JavaScript wants to act on
        methodName - the name of the method JavaScript wants to call
        pendingResultUuid - the uuid of a callback method BACK to JavaScript for returning the result of the call
        json - the parameters to the call as a JSON object
